# Directory structure
data/
venv/

# Code organization rules
sql/              # SQL schema and queries
docs/             # Documentation files
.notes/           # Project notes and planning
tests/            # Test files
src/              # Source code

# Naming conventions
- SQL files: lowercase with underscores (e.g., organization_schema.sql)
- Documentation: lowercase with underscores (e.g., organization_def.md)
- Source files: lowercase with underscores
- Test files: test_*.py for Python test files

# Code style
- SQL: 
  - Keywords in UPPERCASE
  - Indentation: 4 spaces
  - Max line length: 120 characters
  
- Markdown:
  - Use headers properly (h1 -> h6)
  - Code blocks with language specification
  - Links to other docs when relevant

# Documentation rules
- Each major component needs documentation
- README.md in each main directory
- API documentation for all public interfaces
- Update docs when changing schema
- Always consider .notes/ directory content when making changes
- .notes/ directory contains project context and planning information
- Reference relevant .notes/ files in commit messages when applicable

